	<p>We try to record and stream events (lectures, lightning talks, podiums, etc) of the conferences we are present at. We exclude events where the speaker opts out. We provide the following services to our users.</p>

	<h2>At the conference</h2>
	<p>At conferences were eventphone <a href="https://eventphone.de">Eventphone</a> is offering their services, we provide audio feeds via the DECT and GSM network. At conferences where live translation is available, these feeds are also provided this way. Have a look at the <a href="https://eventphone.de/guru2/phonebook">GURU</a> to find out which numbers are used.</p>

	<p>During CCC Congress and Camp we try to offer the video feeds via DVB-T. Checkout <a href="https://twitter.com/c3voc">Twitter</a> for announcements.</p>

	<h2>Live Content</h2>

	<p>Our streams are available on <a href="//streaming.media.ccc.de">streaming.media.ccc.de</a>. We provide the streams in a number of codecs, containers and resolutions and on some conferences even different translations.</p>

	<p>The web player will choses the hopefully right format depending on your operation system and browser. As web browser and video streaming is still broken in <?=h(date('Y'))?>, we recommend to use the streaming client application of choice to consume the streams. We suggest VLC for desktop usage.</p>

	<p>The probably most comfortable way to watch the streams is the <a href="https://github.com/cccc/plugin.video.media-ccc-de">KODI (former XBMC) add-on</a>. This add-on integrates live streams and recordings into a nice media center UI. The add-on is available via the offical kodi add-on repository (<code>Add-ons / Video add-ons / CCC-TV (media.ccc.de)</code>).</p>

	<p>On some conferences we also provide streams of the lounges or content provides of other parties additionally to the main conference program.</p>

	<h2>ReLive Content</h2>
	<p>As soon as a events has started it is also available via our video-on-demand portal (also located on <a href="//streaming.media.ccc.de">streaming.media.ccc.de</a>). This means that you can jump back to the beginning of the event or pause a live event. ReLive provides the same quality as the our live streams. The streams have a lower bitrate than the final recordings to allow people with slow Internet connection to use the streams. There we remove the ReLive "recordings" as soon as the final recoding is released. This has a much better quality and is free of the watermark. Therefor we ask you to not distribute the ReLive recordings but wait for the final releases. More on this topic can be found in this <a href="https://events.ccc.de/2015/01/03/the-youtube-and-stream-dump-problem/">blog post on events.ccc.de</a></p>

	<h2>Recordings</h2>
	<p>The recordings can be found at <a href="https://media.ccc.de">media.ccc.de</a> and in our youtube channel <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/mediacccde">youtube.com/user/mediacccde</a> (in case your preferred device only supports this). Besides our productions you can find content produced by other members of the chaos family on media.ccc.de. Similar to the streamplayer media.ccc.de provides player that tries to play the most suitable format for your OS / browser combination. You can find other formats and links to play in a desktop video player in the "Downloads" tab. Usually also a audio only version is available. All files are also available via an RSS-feed which comes handy with e.g. podcast clients. Our CDN provides metalink which are used by download managers to download in parallel from different CDN servers which can speed up your downloads. Further there is http file listing of the media files on <a href="https://cdn.media.ccc.de">cdn.media.ccc.de</a> which comes handy for binge watching. Also not all content is in the frontend yet but is available via this listing.</p>

	<p>Again we want to point you to the kodi add-on which also lists the recordings. There is also a <a href="https://github.com/cccc/MediaCCC.bundle">plugin for Plex</a> and an <a href="https://github.com/aus-der-Technik/CCC-TV">Apple-TV app</a>.
